quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  16,1,"The command of Allah is at hand, so do not hasten it. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate ňĻwith Him in worshipňļ"
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants, ňĻstating:ňļ ‚ÄúWarn ňĻhumanityňļ that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Me, so be mindful of Me ňĻaloneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  16,3,He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. Exalted is He above what they associate with Him ňĻin worshipňļ
  16,4,"He created humans from a sperm-drop, then‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒthey openly challenge ňĻHimňļ"
  16,5,"And He created the cattle for you as a source of warmth, food, and ňĻmany otherňļ benefits"
  16,6,They are also pleasing to you when you bring them home and when you take them out to graze
  16,7,"And they carry your loads to ňĻdistantňļ lands which you could not otherwise reach without great hardship. Surely your Lord is Ever Gracious, Most Merciful"
  16,8,"ňĻHe also createdňļ horses, mules, and donkeys for your transportation and adornment. And He creates what you do not know"
  16,9,"It is upon Allah ňĻaloneňļ to ňĻclearlyňļ show the Straight Way. Other ways are deviant. Had He willed, He would have easily imposed guidance upon all of you"